After barricading the entrance of the National Assembly from as early as 7:00am, Department of State Security (DSS) operatives have finally allowed the lawmakers into the complex. Senators Rafiu Ibrahim, Biodun Olujimi,  Isa Misau, Abdullahi Gumel, Ben Murray-Bruce have been granted access into the National assembly complex. Honourable Boma Goodhead and a number of House of representatives members were also allowed access into the complex. During the blockade, some lawmakers had found a way into the complex while some of their colleges were still locked out. Journalists and staff of the National assembly, however, are still being locked out of the complex by the DSS. Details later…  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .